<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When zf.sh (zf.bat) generates new source files it breaks some coding style rules.</p>

<p>It uses PHP_EOL as line termination sequence, so using windows version of PHP causes ZF non-compatible code (cite: Line termination follows the Unix text file convention.) Maybe would be better to use unix-like line termintaion or use some setting to specify which line-end symbol to use. Many developers use ZF coding style and zf codegenerator breaks it.</p>

